WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.209 --> 00:00:02.769
Why my reactions feel bigger than the moment,

1
00:00:03.369 --> 00:00:04.849
understanding toxic stress.

2
00:00:06.159 --> 00:00:06.699
Sometimes,

3
00:00:06.840 --> 00:00:09.199
my reactions don't match what's happening around me,

4
00:00:09.520 --> 00:00:10.060
at least

5
00:00:10.199 --> 00:00:11.619
that's how it looks from the outside.

6
00:00:12.510 --> 00:00:14.300
You might see me get angry quickly,

7
00:00:14.550 --> 00:00:15.270
walk away,

8
00:00:15.510 --> 00:00:16.870
or completely shut down.

9
00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:19.819
It might seem like I'm overreacting

10
00:00:20.120 --> 00:00:21.520
or choosing not to listen.

11
00:00:22.200 --> 00:00:24.379
But it doesn't feel like a choice to me.

12
00:00:24.840 --> 00:00:26.879
My brain has learned to stay on alert.

13
00:00:27.549 --> 00:00:29.329
When you've been through a lot of stress,

14
00:00:29.709 --> 00:00:31.180
especially over a long time,

15
00:00:31.389 --> 00:00:34.270
your body gets used to being ready for something to go wrong.

16
00:00:34.630 --> 00:00:35.930
Even when things are calm,

17
00:00:36.110 --> 00:00:37.979
that feeling doesn't just switch off.

18
00:00:38.310 --> 00:00:40.529
There's a part of my brain called the amygdala.

19
00:00:40.790 --> 00:00:43.380
It's there to spot danger and keep me safe.

20
00:00:43.750 --> 00:00:44.650
The problem is,

21
00:00:45.069 --> 00:00:46.650
mine reacts really fast,

22
00:00:47.150 --> 00:00:48.220
sometimes too fast.

23
00:00:48.590 --> 00:00:51.590
So before I've had time to think about what's actually happening,

24
00:00:51.790 --> 00:00:54.250
my body has already decided I'm not safe.

25
00:00:54.659 --> 00:00:56.080
My heart starts racing,

26
00:00:56.299 --> 00:00:57.599
my breathing changes,

27
00:00:58.139 --> 00:00:59.360
everything feels tense.

28
00:00:59.819 --> 00:01:01.700
That's my stress response kicking in.

29
00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:02.409
Fight,

30
00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:03.159
flight,

31
00:01:03.259 --> 00:01:04.050
or freeze.

32
00:01:04.379 --> 00:01:06.680
You might see fight as anger or aggression.

33
00:01:07.019 --> 00:01:08.559
Flight might look like me leaving,

34
00:01:08.779 --> 00:01:09.319
avoiding,

35
00:01:09.419 --> 00:01:10.290
or refusing,

36
00:01:10.540 --> 00:01:11.400
and freeze.

37
00:01:11.660 --> 00:01:13.279
That's when I just shut down.

38
00:01:13.660 --> 00:01:14.569
In those moments,

39
00:01:14.779 --> 00:01:16.400
the thinking part of my brain,

40
00:01:16.580 --> 00:01:18.010
the prefrontal cortex,

41
00:01:18.220 --> 00:01:18.839
goes quiet.

42
00:01:19.819 --> 00:01:22.019
That's the bit that helps me make decisions,

43
00:01:22.569 --> 00:01:23.800
understand consequences,

44
00:01:23.980 --> 00:01:25.720
and process what you're saying.

45
00:01:26.220 --> 00:01:28.410
So when you're asking me to explain myself,

46
00:01:28.580 --> 00:01:29.419
calm down

47
00:01:29.620 --> 00:01:31.080
or think about my behavior.

48
00:01:31.779 --> 00:01:32.980
I probably can't,

49
00:01:33.339 --> 00:01:34.410
not because I won't,

50
00:01:34.860 --> 00:01:35.620
because I can't.

51
00:01:36.410 --> 00:01:38.269
There's also something else going on.

52
00:01:38.730 --> 00:01:40.150
My brain remembers things,

53
00:01:40.330 --> 00:01:42.050
even when I'm not thinking about them.

54
00:01:42.370 --> 00:01:43.430
A tone of voice,

55
00:01:43.629 --> 00:01:44.269
a look,

56
00:01:44.529 --> 00:01:46.330
a situation that feels familiar.

57
00:01:47.059 --> 00:01:50.209
The hippocampus links those things to past experiences,

58
00:01:50.379 --> 00:01:52.980
and suddenly my body reacts like it's happening again.

59
00:01:53.809 --> 00:01:56.300
That's why something small can feel really big.

60
00:01:56.690 --> 00:01:58.110
It's not just about now,

61
00:01:58.370 --> 00:02:00.730
it's about everything my body has learned before.

62
00:02:01.010 --> 00:02:04.319
There's a hormone called cortisol that gets released when I'm stressed.

63
00:02:04.569 --> 00:02:05.080
For me,

64
00:02:05.290 --> 00:02:07.160
that system has been used a lot,

65
00:02:07.449 --> 00:02:09.160
so it doesn't take much to trigger it.

66
00:02:09.449 --> 00:02:11.270
You might see me struggle to focus,

67
00:02:11.410 --> 00:02:12.479
act impulsively,

68
00:02:12.610 --> 00:02:14.149
or get overwhelmed quickly.

69
00:02:14.529 --> 00:02:16.190
That's not about being difficult.

70
00:02:16.449 --> 00:02:18.649
That's what toxic stress does over time.

71
00:02:19.009 --> 00:02:20.389
What really makes a difference

72
00:02:20.770 --> 00:02:21.869
is how you respond.

73
00:02:22.479 --> 00:02:24.059
If voices get louder,

74
00:02:24.240 --> 00:02:25.919
if things feel unpredictable,

75
00:02:26.110 --> 00:02:28.240
or if I feel judged or controlled,

76
00:02:28.559 --> 00:02:30.960
my brain hears that as more danger,

77
00:02:31.279 --> 00:02:33.020
and everything escalates.

78
00:02:33.360 --> 00:02:34.699
But when you stay calm,

79
00:02:35.039 --> 00:02:36.419
when your voice is steady,

80
00:02:36.800 --> 00:02:38.860
when you give me space instead of pressure,

81
00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:40.580
something changes.

82
00:02:40.880 --> 00:02:42.539
My body starts to settle.

83
00:02:42.839 --> 00:02:44.509
I might not show it straight away,

84
00:02:44.759 --> 00:02:45.820
but I feel it.

85
00:02:46.240 --> 00:02:47.639
That's called co-regulation.

86
00:02:48.360 --> 00:02:51.500
I'm borrowing your calm because I don't always have my own yet.

87
00:02:51.839 --> 00:02:52.589
Over time,

88
00:02:52.759 --> 00:02:55.270
that helps me learn how to manage things differently.

89
00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:57.350
You don't need to fix everything for me,

90
00:02:57.720 --> 00:03:00.229
but you do need to understand what's happening underneath,

91
00:03:00.639 --> 00:03:02.259
because what looks like behavior

92
00:03:02.440 --> 00:03:03.669
is often survival.

93
00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:05.600
And when I start to feel safe,

94
00:03:05.990 --> 00:03:06.860
really safe,

95
00:03:07.199 --> 00:03:08.360
that's when I can think,

96
00:03:08.759 --> 00:03:09.259
learn

97
00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:10.660
and begin to trust.